RESTful

	GET = Get request
	POST = Partial update of an object
	PUT = Create new object
	DELETE = Delete object
	
JSON

	HTTP GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /<module>/<function>/<parameters ...>
	<data>

	Module->(Get/Post/Put/Delete)<Function>(<data>, <parameters ...>)
	
SOAP 1.1

	- All WSDL's/Request/Response XML has been verified with SoapUI

	WSDL: /wsdl/<module>
	EndPoint: /soap/<module>

	RESTful to CRUD name conversion:
	GET => READ
	POST => UPDATE
	PUT => CREATE
	DELETE => DELETE
		
	Function name conversion:
	Module->(Create/Read/Update/Delete)<Function>(<data>)

	Example:
	/lim/soap
	Lim->ReadVersion()

Limitations
	- No starting arrays
	- No arrays in arrays

Ports/Services
	Master tcp/5353
	Agent tcp/5354
	Executer tcp/5355




Plugin/Manage Client<->Master<->Agent<->Executore call schema
c=CREATE r=READ u=UPDATE d=DELETE

client   r> master /master/agents
master   r> agent:* /lim
master   <r agent:* { lim: { version: VERSION, type: TYPE } }
client   <r master agent: [ { agent_id: ID, status: ONLINE / OFFLINE, ... }, ... ]

client   r> master /master/agent/{ID}/manages
master   r> agent:ID /agent/manages
agent:ID r> executor /manager
agent:ID <r executor manage: [ { type: TYPE, name: NAME, plugin: PLUGIN, action: [ { action: ACTION, helper: HELPER }, ... ] }, ... ]
master   <r agent:ID manage: [ { type: TYPE, name: NAME, plugin: PLUGIN, action: [ { action: ACTION, helper: HELPER }, ... ] }, ... ]
client   <r master manage: [ { type: TYPE, name: NAME, plugin: PLUGIN, action: [ { action: ACTION, helper: HELPER }, ... ] }, ... ]

client   r> master /master/agent/{ID}/manage/{TYPE}/{NAME}/{PLUGIN}/{ACTION}
master   r> agent:ID /agent/manage/{TYPE}/{NAME}/{PLUGIN}/{ACTION}
agent:ID r> executor /manager/manage/{TYPE}/{NAME}/{PLUGIN}/{ACTION}
agent:ID <r executor { <helper specific data> }
master   <r agent:ID { <helper specific data> }
client   <r master { <helper specific data> }

client   u> master /master/agent/{ID}/manage/{TYPE}/{NAME}/{PLUGIN}/{ACTION} { <helper specific data> }
master   u> agent:ID /agent/manage/{TYPE}/{NAME}/{PLUGIN}/{ACTION} { <helper specific data> }
agent:ID u> executor /manager/manage/{TYPE}/{NAME}/{PLUGIN}/{ACTION} { <helper specific data> }
agent:ID <u executor { <helper specific data> }
master   <u agent:ID { <helper specific data> }
client   <u master { <helper specific data> }

